The paper discusses the application of genetic algorithms (GAs) to optimization problems, which falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the development of appropriate search operators, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of parallel implementation and dynamic exchange of individual representation also suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses numerical experiments, which suggests a possible connection to data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a new variant of GAs, which suggests a possible connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
